1
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:19,100
The company will prepare a welcome party for all new employees.

2
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:20,520
You are no exception.

3
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:23,400
The administrative department has already arranged it.

4
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:26,240
Leave after you've attended it.

5
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,200
Not every departure

6
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:44,800
has a reason,

7
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:45,760
right?

8
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:37,780
A rare company team-building event.

9
00:02:37,780 --> 00:02:38,380
Cheers, cheers!

10
00:02:38,380 --> 00:02:41,580
Come on, come on, cheers, cheers!

11
00:02:43,260 --> 00:02:43,940
You guys don't know,

12
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:46,660
the guy I interviewed last time was even more rowdy than him.

13
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:47,180
Stop talking.

14
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:48,700
There are too many issues with talent agencies now.

15
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:50,220
I don't even want to go anymore.

16
00:02:50,580 --> 00:02:51,260
Sister Zhang.

17
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:54,340
Since when does our company have a welcome party for new hires?

18
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:55,740
Started today, I guess.

19
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:56,940
Today?

20
00:02:57,580 --> 00:02:58,220
No way.

21
00:02:58,460 --> 00:02:59,380
Why?

22
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:00,060
Yeah, right.

23
00:03:00,060 --> 00:03:01,980
We haven't had this benefit for all these years.

24
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:03,440
Who is this newbie anyway?

25
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,640
How would I know?

26
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:06,100
No way, no way.

27
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,300
With such a big show today,

28
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:08,380
the newbie has to perform something.

29
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,540
Li Xingyao, give us a performance!

30
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:10,540
Come on, come on.

31
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:12,580
Give us a performance, Xingyao.

32
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:14,180
Xingyao!

33
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:16,180
Newbies always have to perform.

34
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:17,940
Yeah, come on, come on.

35
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:19,180
Just sing anything.

36
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:19,980
It's fine.

37
00:03:19,980 --> 00:03:21,180
Look, I'll request a simple song for you.

38
00:03:21,420 --> 00:03:22,300
How about "Little Star"?

39
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,260
"Little Star"?

40
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:26,060
Right, even my grandma can sing it.

41
00:03:26,060 --> 00:03:26,620
Come on.

42
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:30,260
Xingyao.

43
00:03:33,140 --> 00:03:33,900
Everyone keep going.

44
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:34,700
Don't mind me.

45
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:39,520
Xingyao, look,

46
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:40,780
Teacher Zhou is here.

47
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:41,860
Come on, in front of the boss,

48
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:43,200
let the boss hear your talent.

49
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:43,660
Exactly.

50
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:44,480
Come on, Xingyao, come on.

51
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:45,220
Come on.

52
00:03:45,220 --> 00:03:54,740
Xingyao!

53
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:58,380
Give us a performance!

54
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:01,580
Xingyao!

55
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:04,060
Give us a performance!

56
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:13,980
Still not singing?

57
00:04:13,980 --> 00:04:15,020
It's okay, Xingyao, just sing.

58
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:16,380
You're already in the beat.

59
00:04:17,460 --> 00:04:19,780
Teacher Xingyao, you can't even sing "Little Star"?

60
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:21,380
Teacher Zhou is here today too.

61
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:24,580
Are you shy or don't want to sing for us?

62
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:26,340
Sing, Xingyao, sing quickly!

63
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:33,340
Li Xingyao, give us a performance!

64
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:41,420
Sorry.

65
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:45,000
I'm going to the bathroom.

66
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:48,500
So lame.

67
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:49,660
It's a rare company team-building.

68
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:51,780
Sigh, forget it. I'll just leave him alone.

69
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:52,540
Come on, come on, cheers.

70
00:04:54,740 --> 00:04:55,900
Teacher Zhou, why did you go out?

71
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:31,080
This song—

72
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,780
I heard it when I was little.

73
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:40,740
Just hummed randomly.

74
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:43,020
Is that so?

75
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:47,300
I thought it might have some special meaning to you.

76
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:53,580
Maybe.

77
00:06:54,940 --> 00:06:56,060
But none of it matters anymore.

78
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:01,580
Your voice—

79
00:07:04,260 --> 00:07:04,980
it's very pure.

80
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,620
Thank you. I'm going back inside.

81
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:12,660
Let me walk you.

82
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:19,540
Um...

83
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:21,940
Have you considered becoming a singer?

84
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:29,540
The company is planning to sign new talent.

85
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,140
Sing my songs.

86
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:35,500
Xiao Yao, you should become a singer in the future.

87
00:08:36,060 --> 00:08:37,620
Xiao Yao, you should become a singer in the future.

88
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:40,140
Do you think I can do it?

89
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,420
Of course. I'm going to write lots and lots of songs,

90
00:08:43,580 --> 00:08:45,460
and have you sing them for me.

91
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,420
Are you interested?

92
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:57,380
Someone as invisible as me,

93
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:00,580
my voice will be forgotten quickly.

94
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:36,180
This is my phone number.

95
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,620
Call me when you've made up your mind.

96
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:42,380
Chances are,

97
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:44,880
we'll never see each other again.

98
00:09:46,780 --> 00:09:47,420
Goodbye.

99
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:03,220
You're back.

100
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:08,260
Someone gave you a ride today?

101
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:15,940
No one important.

102
00:10:17,340 --> 00:10:18,300
Let's go, home.

103
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:30,620
"Never see each other again" —

104
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:32,500
is it because of him?

105
00:11:11,460 --> 00:11:12,420
I went to check out a café today.

106
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,420
Their desserts are really good.

107
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:15,980
I specially brought some back for you to try.

108
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:18,900
Why is your face so red?

109
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:19,700
Are you okay?

110
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:20,900
I'm fine.

111
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,980
Come on, have a taste.

112
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:34,220
Before,

113
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,660
because you sang,

114
00:11:35,980 --> 00:11:37,380
you couldn't eat very sweet things.

115
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:38,780
Now it's fine.

116
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:40,300
Since you're not singing anymore,

117
00:11:40,660 --> 00:11:43,500
I'll bring home the best desserts in the whole world.

118
00:11:43,780 --> 00:11:44,580
Alright?

119
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:49,580
Why are you staring? Eat up.

120
00:12:05,140 --> 00:12:05,740
Xingyao.

121
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,360
Are you —

122
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:09,740
really sure about this?

123
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:24,500
It's no big deal.

124
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:25,500
Xingyao,

125
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:26,620
from now on,

126
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,980
we'll only do things that make us happy.

127
00:12:32,780 --> 00:12:33,580
Xiu Jie.

128
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:36,820
I will live well from now on.

129
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:48,980
It's okay, Xingyao.

130
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:50,620
As long as I'm here,

131
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,300
I promise you won't go hungry.

132
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:13,820
There's someone who loves sweets like crazy,

133
00:13:14,140 --> 00:13:15,740
but for an invisible dream,

134
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,680
forced himself to give up all sugar.

135
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:18,900
Everyone can see

136
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:20,740
that the décor of this shop is very European,

137
00:13:20,740 --> 00:13:21,680
and very exquisite.

138
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,160
Let me show you around.

139
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,640
And then, the desserts everyone cares about most.

140
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:28,920
Their most famous item is this Washington Box.

141
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:31,440
Who would you like to share this sweetness with?

142
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:34,800
So, I wanted to taste the sweetness of this world for him.

143
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:36,800
Just to remember these flavors for him.

144
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,120
Maybe

145
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,880
this is what it's like to care about someone.

146
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:42,700
You can't help

147
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:44,360
but want to experience the world

148
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:45,760
in his way.

149
00:13:46,580 --> 00:13:47,100
Today,

150
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,420
this sea salt cheese —

151
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,400
Star River Entertainment,

152
00:14:09,180 --> 00:14:10,560
Music Director.

153
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:15,280
You are —

154
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:16,720
Xingyao's boss.

155
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,780
Do you have time for a cup of coffee?

156
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:23,840
About Li Xingyao —

157
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,720
I'd like to talk with you.

158
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:44,240
It's him,

159
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:45,320
isn't it?

160
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:48,100
It's Xingyao. How did you —

161
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,140
The company is signing new artists.

162
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:53,980
I plan to promote him.

163
00:14:55,860 --> 00:14:56,480
Really?

164
00:14:56,860 --> 00:14:57,600
That's great!

165
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:59,580
Xingyao's voice is a gift,

166
00:14:59,660 --> 00:15:01,020
pure and full of storytelling.

167
00:15:01,220 --> 00:15:03,300
These days, singers in the market all rely on technique.

168
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,620
What's missing is someone like him.

169
00:15:11,940 --> 00:15:12,920
It's a pity.

170
00:15:13,340 --> 00:15:15,340
Xingyao said he will never sing again.

171
00:15:15,980 --> 00:15:16,620
Why?

172
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,160
Xingyao, he —

173
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:21,640
is probably really tired.

174
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:30,940
You seem to know him especially well.

175
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:32,560
Of course.

176
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,520
I am the person who knows him best in this world.

177
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:43,660
What is your relationship with him?

178
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,200
Before signing an artist,

179
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,920
I need to understand all of the artist's peripheral relationships.

180
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,800
He and I grew up in the same orphanage.

181
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:01,880
We depended on each other.

182
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,000
What orphanage?

183
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:35,880
It was around the year he turned fourteen.

184
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:37,960
His parents got into a car accident

185
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:39,840
and passed away.

186
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,480
After he was brought in,

187
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,260
he wouldn't speak all day.

188
00:16:46,460 --> 00:16:47,920
He'd just cry while staring at the trees outside the window.

189
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:51,160
He was physically weak,

190
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:53,160
and his personality was withdrawn.

191
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:55,680
The other children in the orphanage

192
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,720
always liked to bully him.

193
00:16:59,340 --> 00:16:59,840
No —

194
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:01,860
to be exact,

195
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,240
it was bullying.

196
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:07,200
After that,

197
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:09,840
he started to be afraid of people.

198
00:17:11,180 --> 00:17:12,400
It got worse and worse.

199
00:17:18,220 --> 00:17:20,360
It was me who didn't keep the promise.

200
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:23,080
Xiao Yao, will you blame me?
